  # AABB
  
  func AABB(position: Vector3, size: Vector3) -> AABB
  
  class AABB:

  # The above reference is not syntactically correct GDScript:
  #     - Constants must be assigned immediately, but 'INF' and 'NAN' cannot be defined in GDScript.
  #     - Methods cannot be declared without a definition, ofcourse.
  #     - Methods cannot be overloaded, but I wanted to show the constructors for the builtin classes.
  #     - 'Variant' is not actually defined in the API, but is used in type hints for clearity; esp. return types.
  #     - Enums cannot be used in type hints, but again add clearity.
  # Also remember:
  #     - Members of singleton classes are effectively static.
  #     - Enum constants defined in GDScript must be prefixed by their enum name, but in the API they are just class contants.
